This paper proposes a method for 3D facial structure reconstruction and dense alignment using a Convolutional Neural Network. The paper focuses on computer vision and graphics, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of UV space and weight masks could suggest that the paper belongs to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. The paper also involves the processing of images, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a loss function, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
